    "留学"
  ],
  "status": "active",
  "status_note_md": {
    "en": "The official Study in Japan portal states that residential status for studies at universities, junior colleges, colleges of technology, specialized training colleges or Japanese language schools is designated as Student, with a period of stay determined by the Minister of Justice not exceeding 4 years and 3 months.",
    "zh-Hans": "官方 Study in Japan 门户说明，在大学、短期大学、高等专门学校、专修学校或日语学校学习时的在留资格为“留学”，居留期限由法务大臣决定，最长不超过 4 年 3 个月。"
  },
  "summary_md": {
    "en": "Japan's main study residence status for school-based learning. Applicants usually obtain a Certificate of Eligibility through the school, then a visa at a Japanese mission, and receive a residence card after entry when staying more than three months.",
    "zh-Hans": "日本面向学校学习的主要留学在留资格。申请人通常通过学校申请在留资格认定证明书，再向日本使领馆申请签证，停留超过三个月时入境后领取在留卡。"
  },
  "good_for_md": {
    "en": "International students accepted by an eligible Japanese school who can show funds for expenses during the stay and complete the COE and visa process.",
    "zh-Hans": "适合获日本合资格学校录取、能证明在留期间费用，并完成认定证明书与签证流程的国际学生。"
  },
  "not_good_for_md": {
    "en": "Applicants without a school place, people seeking unrestricted work only, or remote-work digital-nomad stays under a different status. Japan has a separate Designated Activities digital-nomad route.",
    "zh-Hans": "不适合没有学校录取、仅寻求不受限制工作，或希望通过其他身份远程工作的申请人。日本另有特定活动数字游民途径。"
  },
  "pathway_mechanism": "other",
